
# .gitkeep

# This file is intentionally empty and committed to ensure the `public/`
# directory is tracked by Git even when it contains no other files.
#
# File names:
# - public/.gitkeep
#
# Usage:
# - Do not remove this file unless you intend to remove the `public/`
#   directory from version control.
# - Add static assets (HTML, CSS, JS, images) to this directory as needed.
